        {
            "id": 100,
            "label": "Light Sensor Calibrated Coefficient",
            "description": "Calibration coefficient for light measurements",
            "overview": "<p>This configuration defines the calibrated scale for ambient light intensity. Because the method and position that the sensor mounted and the cover of sensor will bring measurement error, user can get more real light intensity by this parameter setting. User should run the steps as blows for calibrating:<\/p> <ol><li>Set this parameter value to default (Assumes the sensor has been added in a Z- Wave Network).<\/li> <li>Place a digital luxmeter close to sensor and keep the same direction, monitor the light intensity value (Vm) which report to controller and record it. The same time user should record the value (Vs) of luxmeter.<\/li> <li>The scale calibration formula: k = Vm \/ Vs.<\/li> <li>The value of k is then multiplied by 1024 and rounded to the nearest whole number.<\/li> <li>Set the value getting in 5) to this parameter, calibrate finished.<\/li> <\/ol><p>For example, Vm = 300, Vs = 2600, then k = 2600 \/ 300 = 8.6667,<br \/>k = 8.6667 * 1024 = 8874.7 \u2248 8875. In this case, the parameter should be set to 8875.<\/p>",
            "size": 2,
            "bitmask": "00000000",
            "default": 1024,
            "read_only": false,
            "write_only": false,
            "value_min": 1,
            "value_max": 32767,
            "options": []
        }
